control construction: fixed monoalphabetic substitution of a low-successor structured source; same structured source under a position-dependent additive alphabet permutation.

Interpretation: the original seven-row unconstrained shuffle table has pointwise exceedances in H(next) add-1 bits (p=0.400000), H(next|cur) add-1 bits (p=0.400000), MI add-1 bits (p=0.400000), transition chi2 (p=0.400000), successor edges (p=0.400000), successor entropy (p=0.400000), FSM lower bound (p=0.400000).
Diagonal confound: the accepted eye order has 0 adjacent-equal self-transitions, while the unconstrained shuffle null averages 12.00 with 95% 11..12. Those raw exceedances are therefore dominated by the already-known zero-adjacency constraint.
Dropping diagonal cells alone leaves unconstrained-shuffle diagnostic flags in offdiag transition chi2 (p=0.400000), offdiag successor edges (p=0.400000); this is not the final control because that null still permits adjacent repeats.
After conditioning the shuffle null on zero adjacent-equal pairs, pointwise flags remain in MI add-1 bits (p=0.400000), offdiag transition chi2 (p=0.400000), offdiag successor edges (p=0.400000). Treat them as a tiny residual arrangement effect with negligible effect size (corrected MI near zero, below), not novel first-order memory.
Effect size: corrected MI is 0.000726 bits (1.139e-4 of the 6.375-bit maximum); raw plug-in MI exceeds the flat-random null mean by 0.174 bits and collapses to -0.019171 bits after correction.
Sparse-table caveat: 6889/6889 Pearson expected cells are <1 (<5: 6889), with mean 0.149; the asymptotic chi-square df=6724 tail is invalid. The Pearson value 8481.321 is a sparse-table inflation artifact relative to G=2*N*MI: 4202.5 from raw MLE MI and 1.034 after add-1 correction.
Raw unconstrained exceedances are dominated by the known zero-adjacency constraint (above). Any exceedances that survive the no-repeat-conditioned null are not attributable to zero-adjacency (that null controls it) nor to table sparsity (those tails are empirical, not asymptotic); they reflect only a tiny residual arrangement effect whose honest effect size is negligible (corrected MI near zero, above). None of this is a plaintext/decryption claim or evidence of novel first-order memory. The planted controls still verify directionality for truly first-order-structured fixtures.
